result.name: Lung Fung Garden

reviews.text:
Very conveniently located for residents between Shek Wu Hui old town centre, wet market, all of the local malls and country park. The 3 residential blocks are intersected by a busy walkthrough full of stalls and hidden alleys with media/clothing/jewellery stores, giving you a mini Ladies Market experience.

The shops are more akin to those found in the old centre rather than modern malls, catering to more basic needs (laundry, hairdressing, fresh fruit & veg), saving locals from having to cross the road into the old centre.

Yes, cross border traffic gets annoying and there are too many pharmacies useless to locals. Can't argue it's extremely busy/popular though.
